summary: i cant see any sign of needle in any of the photos of arya n i am DISTRESSED HALP. istg if needle explodes during the battle i...
question: i cant see any sign of needle in any of the photos of arya n i am DISTRESSED HALP. istg if needle explodes during the battle i will cRy (also i shouldnt be this attached to a SWORD)
answer:
Hey!

I had another look and you’re right, she’s not holding needle but the Valyrian steel dagger. I’m going to hope that it is just a fashion choice for the photoshoot. I can’t imagine Arya not having Needle, it’s such an important part of her character/character development. 

Although, having said that, Needle represented Jon Snow and home. Now that she’s back home and will reunite with Jon Snow, what Needle symbolized to her, will be there in the flesh. Of course, the sword is still awesome but that could be the reasoning behind that. 

Fingers crossed and it’s just for the photoshoop. 

By the way, at least Needle is real, I’m attached to non-existent CGI dragons. So… it’ s all relative.

summary: At the forge she found the fires extinguished and the doors closed and barred. She crept in a window, as she had once before....
text:
At the forge she found the fires extinguished and the doors closed and barred. She crept in a window, as she had once before. Gendry shared a mattress with two other apprentice smiths. She crouched in the loft for a long time before her eyes adjusted enough for her to be sure that he was the one on the end. Then she put a hand over his mouth and pinched him. His eyes opened. He could not have been very deeply asleep. “Please,” she whispered. She took her hand off his mouth and pointed.
For a moment she did not think he understood, but then he slid out from under the blankets. Naked, he padded across the room, shrugged into a loose roughspun tunic, and climbed down from the loft after her. The other sleepers did not stir. “What do you want now?” Gendry said in a low angry voice.
“A sword.”

body:
Here is the thing about this group picture… if Jon and Daenerys were the two main characters of the story, then they would’ve been front and centre of this picture.


They are not.

The Starks are… Sansa, Arya and Bran are.

And that should tell you all about Season 8!

A Time For Wolves.
